cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.MM, cs.SOC

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the propagation and influence of memes across multiple web communities. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper describes the processing pipeline used to detect and measure the propagation of memes. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper discusses the impact of memes on public opinion and politics. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper analyzes a dataset of 160M images. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also relevant as the paper studies the behavior of web communities and their reciprocal influence.
